  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Providing Emergency Multipurpose Cash Grants (MCG) and WASH Services to support the most flood-affected people in particular the elderly in Kurigram District in Bangladesh</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">8000 Flood affected people have financial means to meet their basic immediate needs such as food, shelter repairing, hygiene , health, education, livelihood inputs, transports and other non-food items.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">8000 people will have access to WASH items who benefit from the distribution of Family hygiene kits.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This project will target vulnerable groups per it&apos;s vulnerability criteria such as female headed households, pregnant and lactating women, elderly, children, disabled. Particular emphasis will be placed on displaced populations and those who have lost their shelter. RI and its partners will engage with local communities to identify extremely marginalized and poor families of the target communities who have been severely affected by the flooding and lost standing crops, sanitation facilities, food stock, livestock resources and livelihoods assets. Female Headed Households, elderly people, persons with disability and children will also be targeted for the proposed activities as indicated above. Vulnerable households who do not have access to mobile banking will be able to benefit from physical cash distributions.</narrative>
  </description>
